<subSubSection id="C36965D095621872FF33B38E1190187E" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="30" pageId="6" pageNumber="29" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCC365B95621873FF33B38E17331FF9" blockId="6.[166,1225,1714,1837]" pageId="6" pageNumber="29">
D i s t r i b u t i o n. Transpalaearctic region. In particular: 
<collectingCountry id="F36476CB95621873FC9CB38F10911FD9" box="[884,980,1714,1740]" name="Ukraine" pageId="6" pageNumber="29">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
(the 
<collectingRegion id="49B7F8B995621873FBF9B38F17281FD8" box="[1041,1133,1714,1741]" country="Ukraine" name="Crimea" pageId="6" pageNumber="29">Crimea</collectingRegion>
), 
<collectingCountry id="F36476CB95621873FB68B38F17811FD9" box="[1152,1220,1714,1740]" name="Spain" pageId="6" pageNumber="29">Spain</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F36476CB95621873FF4EB3EF13BF1FF9" box="[166,250,1746,1772]" name="Greece" pageId="6" pageNumber="29">Greece</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F36476CB95621873FEEDB3EF12111FF9" box="[261,340,1746,1772]" name="Russia" pageId="6" pageNumber="29">Russia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F36476CB95621873FEB7B3EF128F1FF9" box="[351,458,1746,1772]" name="Armenia" pageId="6" pageNumber="29">Armenia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F36476CB95621873FE3CB3EF111E1FF9" box="[468,603,1746,1772]" name="Uzbekistan" pageId="6" pageNumber="29">Uzbekistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F36476CB95621873FD8EB3EF10541FF9" box="[614,785,1746,1772]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="6" pageNumber="29">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F36476CB95621873FCF4B3EF101A1FF9" box="[796,863,1746,1772]" name="Israel" pageId="6" pageNumber="29">Israel</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F36476CB95621873FC81B3EF10B71FF9" box="[873,1010,1746,1772]" name="Turkey" pageId="6" pageNumber="29">Asia Minor</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F36476CB95621873FC15B3EF17371FF9" box="[1021,1138,1746,1772]" name="Mongolia" pageId="6" pageNumber="29">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC365B95621873FF33B3CE17D11E38" blockId="6.[166,1225,1714,1837]" pageId="6" pageNumber="29">
D i a g n o s i s. Wingspan 
<quantity id="4C8B9BBE95621873FDF9B3CF11DD1E18" box="[529,664,1778,1805]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="16.5" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="15.0">15–18 mm</quantity>
. Forewing color is variable, forewing pattern suffused whitish scales, blurred dark spot is present near the middle of wing (
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95621873FBC5B22F172F1E39" box="[1069,1130,1810,1836]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[169,202,1298,1320]" captionTargetBox="[322,1064,148,1221]" captionTargetId="figure-179@6.[317,1074,148,1230]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 6. Ypsolopha albiramella: 1 — moth (habitus, dorsal); 2 — male genitalia (lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414514" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414514/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="29">fig. 6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95621873FB9DB22F17C61E39" box="[1141,1155,1810,1836]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[174,207,1408,1430]" captionTargetBox="[325,1069,174,1369]" captionTargetId="figure-159@1.[321,1078,171,1383]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1. Argyresthia kurenzovi: 1 — forewing pattern; 2–4 — male genitalia (2 — ventral view, 3 — ventral plate, 4 — aedeagus); 5 — female genitalia; 6 — bursa copulatrix with signum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414497" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414497/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="B907EA4995621873FB9DB22F17C61E39" box="[1141,1155,1810,1836]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="29">1</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC365B95631872FF36B58C175819F9" blockId="7.[169,1228,177,389]" pageId="7" pageNumber="30">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95631872FE7DB58C129119DE" box="[405,468,177,203]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[169,202,1298,1320]" captionTargetBox="[322,1064,148,1221]" captionTargetId="figure-179@6.[317,1074,148,1230]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 6. Ypsolopha albiramella: 1 — moth (habitus, dorsal); 2 — male genitalia (lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414514" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414514/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="30">fig. 6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95631872FE09B58C12AA19DE" box="[481,495,177,203]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1105,1127]" captionTargetBox="[322,1065,191,1089]" captionTargetId="figure-253@2.[317,1074,174,1089]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2. Argyresthia communana: 1 — forewing pattern; 2–4 — male genitalia (2 — ventral plate, 3 — valva, 4 — aedeagus); 5 — bursa copulatrix." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414501" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414501/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="B907EA4995631872FE09B58C12AA19DE" box="[481,495,177,203]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="30">2</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Valva of elongated — oval shape. Saccus more than 2 times shorter than valva. Aedeagus stout, more than 1.5 times longer than saccus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC365B95631872FF36B5CF12CF1859" blockId="7.[169,1228,177,389]" pageId="7" pageNumber="30">R e m a r k s. This species can be recognized by the forewing pattern and by the male genitalia structure, particularly by the broadened aedeagus which is more than 1.5 times longer than saccus.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC365B95631872FF36B46C1190187E" blockId="7.[169,1228,177,389]" box="[222,725,337,363]" pageId="7" pageNumber="30">
Recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="F36476CB95631872FE7EB46C114D187E" box="[406,520,337,363]" name="Mongolia" pageId="7" pageNumber="30">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
for the first time.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
